.TH WL-DOCK 1 "2026-07-20" "wl-dock 0.5.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wl-dock \- Wayland dock for wlroots-based compositors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wl-dock
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wl-dock
is a lightweight dock for Wayland compositors implementing the
wlr-layer-shell and wlr-foreign-toplevel-management protocols. It is
primarily designed and tested against Labwc, but also works on sway,
Hyprland and other wlroots-based compositors.
.PP
The dock shows one button per toplevel window with its application icon,
a system tray area hosting SNI (StatusNotifierItem) hosts such as
fcitx5, and a clock widget. Auto-hide on mouse leave is supported.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a brief usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the program version and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-icon\-theme " NAME"
Override the icon theme used by
.BR QIcon::fromTheme ().
Useful when the desktop icon theme does not contain certain application
icons; for example
.BR "wl-dock --icon-theme Papirus" .
.TP
.BI \-\-default\-icon " NAME"
Fallback icon name (a freedesktop icon theme entry) used when no
.B .desktop
file can be resolved for an
.IR app_id .
Defaults to
.BR application-x-executable .
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DISPLAY
Ignored on Wayland; kept only for compatibility.
.TP
.B WAYLAND_DISPLAY
The Wayland display socket to connect to. If unset, the default
"wayland-0" is used.
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME ", " XDG_DATA_DIRS
Used to locate
.B .desktop
files and icons. See the
.BR XDG Base Directory Specification .
.TP
.B DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS
The D-Bus session bus address used by the SNI tray host. The
.B org.kde.StatusNotifierWatcher
service is registered on this bus.
.TP
.B QT_LOGGING_RULES
Enables per-category debug logging. Useful categories include:
.RS
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B dock.ctrl
\(en DockController lifecycle
.IP \(bu 2
.B dock.ftm
\(en foreign-toplevel manager events
.IP \(bu 2
.B dock.icon
\(en .desktop / icon resolution
.IP \(bu 2
.B dock.window
\(en DockWindow geometry / hide state
.IP \(bu 2
.B dock.sni
\(en SNI watcher / item lifecycle
.IP \(bu 2
.B dock.sni.menu
\(en DBusMenu rendering
.IP \(bu 2
.B dock.sni.menu.popup
\(en SniMenu positioning / screen selection
.RE
.RE
.PP
Example:
.PP
.RS
.EX
QT_LOGGING_RULES="dock.sni=true;dock.icon=true" wl-dock
.EE
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/wl-dock
Executable.
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/wl-dock.desktop
Desktop entry.
.TP
.I /usr/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/wl-dock.svg
Application icon.
.TP
.I /usr/share/man/man1/wl-dock.1.gz
This manual page.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit (currently the dock runs until killed).
.TP
.B 1
Initialisation failure, e.g. cannot connect to the Wayland display or
the foreign-toplevel protocol is not supported by the compositor.
.SH NOTES
The dock is designed to run as a single instance per Wayland session.
Multiple docks are created automatically in a multi-monitor setup, one
per output.
.SH BUGS
Please report issues at the project repository.
.SH AUTHOR
The wl-dock project.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR labwc (1),
.BR sway (1),
.BR hyprland (1),
.BR wayland (7)
